  "prompt": "How much money can I deposit in my account?",
  "response": "The amount you can deposit into your account depends on several factors, including the policies of your bank or financial institution, the type of account you have, and any regulatory limits that may apply. Most banks do not have a maximum limit for deposits, particularly for checking or savings accounts. However, some accounts may have restrictions or fees associated with large deposits.\n\nIt's best to check directly with your bank for their specific deposit policies, or refer to your account agreement for more details. If you're considering a large deposit, it may also be worthwhile to inquire about any potential reporting requirements or holds that could apply.",
